Description of code: 

The first breadboard represents toilet roll 1 and the bottom breadboard represents toilet roll 2.

Assume distance from an empty roll surface to the ultrasonic sensor is 60cm and from a full roll surface to ultrasonic sensor is 30cm

When both rolls are full, both green LEDS light up only

So then the user starts using roll 1 first, Green LED on both rolls continues staying on.

When the distance reaches 45cm for roll 1, its Green LED offs and its red LED lights up. No change for roll 2 yet.

Finally when distance for roll 1 reaches 60cm, the servo motor turns 270 degrees and the Roll 1 LED stays red until a new roll is inserted (Ill talk abt how I want the code to be for when inserting new toilet rolls)

So then now the second roll is in use and the Green LED still stays on

When the distance reaches 45cm, its Green LED offs and its yellow LED turns on

When the distance reaches 50cm, its Yellow LED offs and its Red LED turns on

Finally when distance for roll 2 reaches 60cm, the servo motor turns back 270 degrees and the Roll 2 LED stays red until a new roll is inserted

